ibis.ipl.registry

Class NullRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • ibis.ipl.registry.Registry
      • ibis.ipl.registry.NullRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ibis.ipl.Manageable, ibis.ipl.Registry

    public final class NullRegistry
extends Registry
    Registry implementation that does nothing. Throws an Exception most calls.

        public NullRegistry(ibis.ipl.IbisCapabilities capabilities,
                    ibis.ipl.RegistryEventHandler handler,

                    byte[] data,
                    java.lang.String implementationVersion,
                    ibis.ipl.Credentials credentials,
                    byte[] tag)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a Null Registry.
        Parameters:
        capabilities - the required capabilities
        handler - registry handler to pass events to.
        properties - properties of this registry.
        data - Ibis implementation data to attach to the IbisIdentifier.
        tag - A tag provided by the application for this ibis instance.
        implementationVersion - the identification of this ibis implementation, including version, class and such. Must be identical for all ibises in a single pool.
        credentials - the credentials
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - in case of trouble.
        ibis.ipl.IbisConfigurationException - In case invalid properties were given.
